## **Description**
The **Web Service **operator allows to call a web service and return the response of the selected method.

> Warning

Before using the Web Service operator, you must define at least a Web Service resource and add it to the Data Transformation project, importing a WSDL file compliant with the Simple Object Access Protocol (SOAP) grammar 1.1.

For more information, see [DT3 Web Service Component](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-web-service-component).

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in0**

Any

The value to use for the corresponding parameter of the web service method

**in...**

Any

N-th input node, containing the value for the corresponding parameter of the web service method

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**out0**

String

The data obtained from the web service call.

## **Settings**
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)	

- From the **Web Service **drop-down menu, select the Web Service resource that you want to use.

> Note

For more information, see: [DT3 Web Service Component.](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-web-service-component)

- From the list of **Methods**, select the web service method that the operator will call.

- In the **In case of failure **area, select the desired behavior in case of errors while calling the web service:

**Exit with error**: The DTE software service will stop and return an error message in output.

- **Proceed without emitting a value**: The DTE software service will continue without returning any error messages.

- Click **Apply **to confirm.
